cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new approach to reinforcement learning by incorporating unsupervised auxiliary tasks. It also involves the use of deep neural networks for representation learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of an agent that can learn multiple tasks simultaneously and adapt to the most relevant aspects of the actual task. 

The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques for processing visual input, which could place it in the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

As the agent is designed to perform tasks in a three-dimensional environment, it could also belong to the category of cs.RO (Robotics). 

Finally, the use of reinforcement learning and deep neural networks for learning could also place this paper in the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
